{"amendments":[{"body":"Persist the requested invocation metadata on artifact records instead of only enriching `producer`: add a serde-defaulted `invocation_metadata` field with `backend_family` and `model_id`, thread `InvocationEnvelope.metadata.backend_used.family` and `InvocationEnvelope.metadata.model_used.model_id` through the artifact persistence helpers, and let `FsPayloadArtifactWriteStore` serialize it into `history/artifacts/*.json`.","rationale":"`src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs` currently has no `invocation_metadata` field on `ArtifactRecord`, and `src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs` only maps the envelope values into `RecordProducer`. Since `src/adapters/fs.rs` just serializes the record as-is, the persisted artifact JSON still cannot expose the fields requested in the prompt."},{"body":"Replace or extend the regression coverage so it asserts `invocation_metadata.backend_family` and `invocation_metadata.model_id` on a persisted artifact produced by the stage artifact path, rather than asserting only `producer.backend_family` / `producer.model_id` on final-review panel artifacts.","rationale":"The current test in `src/contexts/workflow_composition/final_review.rs` exercises final-review supporting-record persistence, not the `engine.rs` stage persistence path called out in the prompt, and it only checks `producer`. That test would not catch the requested contract gap."}],"summary":"Found two blocking issues: artifact JSON still lacks `invocation_metadata.backend_family` / `model_id`, and the added regression only checks pre-existing `producer` metadata on a final-review panel path instead of the stage artifact persistence path."}